Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Finely chop a few @sliced dill pickle{1%unit} slices until you have 2 tsp. (Save remaining pickle slices for serving.) Drain and rinse @kidney beans{1%unit}. Trim and mince @scallions{2%unit}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @sliced dill pickle{1%unit}(chopped), 1⁄2 tsp @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

Heat a dry, large pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce} and cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a #paper towel{} lined #plate{}. Carefully discard bacon fat; wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, place half the beans (all for 4 servings) in a large #bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth. (It's OK if there are still some larger pieces.)

Stir in @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, scallions, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @tempura mix{82%g}, @Cajun spice blend{2%tsp}, and 2 TBSP @water{2%tbsp} until thoroughly combined. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Divide bean mixture into two mounds (four mounds for 4).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Using a #silicone spatula{}, add bean mixture mounds to pan and gently press to flatten into patties, each about as wide as a burger bun. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to a plate. 

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil before each batch.

Use pan used for bacon here.

Halve and toast @brioche buns{2%unit} until golden; spread cut sides with @butter{2%tbsp}. Spread bottom buns with up to half the secret sauce. Fill buns with patties and as much sliced pickle as you like.

Top patties with bacon.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with potato wedges and remaining secret sauce on the side.